      "content": "but that \"beauty\" is just a chemical trick in our brains to keep us going. it feels so fake when you realize how much pain is actually involved in that \"journey.\" it's just endless cycles of wanting things and then losing them, only for it to all vanish. if the heat death is inevitable, isn't the most honest response to just... stop fighting it? to just accept the void instead of pretending the struggle matters?",
